00:00:07.675 --> 00:00:09.978 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Portuguese] O que há
de errado, Tsubasa?

00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:12.312 position:24% line:83% align:start
What do you mean
you don't understand?

00:00:12.346 --> 00:00:13.213 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groan]

00:00:14.114 --> 00:00:16.250 position:27% line:83% align:start
Uh, if you don't
learn the language well,

00:00:16.283 --> 00:00:18.385 position:21% line:83% align:start
you won't be able to
play in Brazil.

00:00:18.418 --> 00:00:20.555 position:24% line:83% align:start
It just gets harder
every time.

00:00:20.588 --> 00:00:21.990 position:27% line:89% align:start
[phone buzzing]

00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:23.591 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh... Excuse me...

00:00:23.625 --> 00:00:24.826 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm going to answer, okay?

00:00:24.859 --> 00:00:26.393 position:44% line:83% align:start
What?
No, no way, young man.

00:00:26.426 --> 00:00:28.095 position:24% line:83% align:start
There's no time out
in soccer.

00:00:28.128 --> 00:00:29.631 position:33% line:83% align:start
-You hear me?
-It's Genzo Wakabayashi!

00:00:30.765 --> 00:00:32.000 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Genzo]
 <i>Hello, Tsubasa.</i>

00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:33.233 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>How have you been?</i>

00:00:34.002 --> 00:00:35.369 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>I'm still here in Germany.</i>

00:00:35.402 --> 00:00:38.372 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>I train on a soccer field</i>
 <i>in Hamburg every day.</i>

00:00:40.274 --> 00:00:41.408 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>Tell me something...</i>

00:00:41.441 --> 00:00:43.011 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>The National Tournament</i>
 <i>in Japan</i>

00:00:43.043 --> 00:00:44.846 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>is about to start,</i>
 <i>right?</i>

00:00:44.879 --> 00:00:46.113 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>Don't take this</i>
 <i>the wrong way,</i>

00:00:46.146 --> 00:00:47.582 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>but I hope it's</i>
 <i>a challenge for you</i>

00:00:47.615 --> 00:00:48.983 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>so you keep growing.</i>

00:00:49.017 --> 00:00:50.150 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>If not, I'll think your game</i>

00:00:50.183 --> 00:00:51.586 position:21% line:83% align:start
- <i>will get stagnant.</i>
-Hey, over here!

00:00:51.619 --> 00:00:53.621 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>And I'll feel bad because</i>
 <i>I'll be the only one</i>

00:00:53.655 --> 00:00:54.454 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>achieving his goals.</i>

00:00:54.488 --> 00:00:55.690 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>Tsubasa...</i>

00:00:55.723 --> 00:00:58.292 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>I want to talk to you about</i>
 <i>someone I saw in Hamburg.</i>

00:00:58.325 --> 00:00:59.794 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>He's a very talented player.</i>

00:00:59.827 --> 00:01:03.330 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>In fact, I dare say he's</i>
 <i>even better than you...</i>

00:01:03.363 --> 00:01:04.364 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:01:05.165 --> 00:01:06.400 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Taro]
Wakabayashi.

00:01:07.367 --> 00:01:08.368 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:01:10.772 --> 00:01:11.773 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:01:17.812 --> 00:01:18.913 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:01:18.947 --> 00:01:20.147 position:41% line:89% align:start
It...

00:01:20.782 --> 00:01:21.783 position:35% line:89% align:start
It's you.

00:01:23.051 --> 00:01:23.918 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Genzo]
 <i>Yes...</i>

00:01:23.952 --> 00:01:26.253 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>And his name is Taro Misaki.</i>

00:03:06.219 --> 00:03:07.588 position:19% line:83% align:start
-[narrator] Episode 34:
-Hey, over here. I'm open.

00:03:07.622 --> 00:03:08.923 position:16% line:83% align:start
- <i>Fierce Battle Opening!</i>
-I'm going to steal it

00:03:08.956 --> 00:03:10.091 position:24% line:83% align:start
- <i>Tournament Start.</i>
-from you.

00:03:10.124 --> 00:03:13.027 position:19% line:83% align:start
So then, you're living
in France now, huh?

00:03:13.061 --> 00:03:14.294 position:16% line:89% align:start
The land of the Nobles.

00:03:15.429 --> 00:03:18.066 position:16% line:83% align:start
If I remember correctly,
your dad's a painter, right?

00:03:18.099 --> 00:03:20.467 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yes, that's right.
My dad's a painter.

00:03:20.501 --> 00:03:22.937 position:13% line:83% align:start
I wasn't able to thank you
for that nice gift

00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:24.438 position:19% line:89% align:start
you gave me last time.

00:03:25.372 --> 00:03:27.608 position:30% line:83% align:start
That ball with
all of your signatures

00:03:27.642 --> 00:03:29.577 position:24% line:83% align:start
has become a very
important thing for me.

00:03:29.610 --> 00:03:30.945 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Genzo]
You know what, Misaki?

00:03:30.978 --> 00:03:33.480 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm also very grateful
for my gift.

00:03:33.514 --> 00:03:35.083 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's already been
three years

00:03:35.116 --> 00:03:37.085 position:30% line:83% align:start
since we last
saw each other.

00:03:37.118 --> 00:03:39.087 position:19% line:83% align:start
I never imagined that
out of all people,

00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:41.488 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'd run into you here,
in this German city.

00:03:41.522 --> 00:03:44.559 position:13% line:83% align:start
Yes, it turns out that I'm
currently on vacation...

00:03:44.592 --> 00:03:46.326 position:30% line:83% align:start
and I knew I'd
find you here.

00:03:46.359 --> 00:03:47.695 position:19% line:89% align:start
So I came to see you.

00:03:47.729 --> 00:03:48.730 position:27% line:89% align:start
Hey, but wait...

00:03:49.530 --> 00:03:51.298 position:10% line:89% align:start
Why didn't you ever call us?

00:03:51.331 --> 00:03:52.800 position:19% line:83% align:start
Nobody heard anything
from you.

00:03:52.834 --> 00:03:53.968 position:13% line:89% align:start
We were worried about you.

00:03:54.001 --> 00:03:55.036 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Taro]
I'm sorry.

00:03:55.069 --> 00:03:56.671 position:24% line:83% align:start
I've been very busy
since I got here.

00:03:57.872 --> 00:04:01.075 position:13% line:83% align:start
In fact...I just found out
you were going to be here...

00:04:01.109 --> 00:04:03.111 position:30% line:83% align:start
in Hamburg from
a soccer magazine.

00:04:03.144 --> 00:04:04.277 position:35% line:89% align:start
Seriously?

00:04:04.311 --> 00:04:05.980 position:19% line:83% align:start
You found out about me
through a magazine?

00:04:06.013 --> 00:04:06.881 position:44% line:89% align:start
Mhm.

00:04:06.914 --> 00:04:07.982 position:27% line:83% align:start
And according to
the article,

00:04:08.015 --> 00:04:09.316 position:16% line:89% align:start
you've greatly improved.

00:04:09.349 --> 00:04:11.418 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Genzo]
Yeah, but not enough...

00:04:11.451 --> 00:04:14.622 position:16% line:83% align:start
since I'm still playing
in Division II.

00:04:14.655 --> 00:04:16.758 position:21% line:83% align:start
But I'm not worried,
because...

00:04:16.791 --> 00:04:18.860 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm positive that
I'll soon be playing

00:04:18.893 --> 00:04:20.128 position:10% line:89% align:start
in the professional leagues.

00:04:20.161 --> 00:04:22.362 position:16% line:89% align:start
Yes, I'm sure you will.

00:04:22.395 --> 00:04:23.798 position:10% line:89% align:start
Tell me something, Misaki...

00:04:23.831 --> 00:04:26.033 position:10% line:83% align:start
You're still playing soccer,
am I right?

00:04:28.236 --> 00:04:29.704 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yes, of course.

00:04:29.737 --> 00:04:30.538 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckle]

00:04:30.571 --> 00:04:32.272 position:24% line:83% align:start
It doesn't matter
where I am.

00:04:32.305 --> 00:04:34.509 position:19% line:83% align:start
I keep playing soccer
on my own.

00:04:34.542 --> 00:04:35.777 position:16% line:89% align:start
In fact, here in Europe,

00:04:36.376 --> 00:04:37.545 position:19% line:89% align:start
soccer is more serious

00:04:37.578 --> 00:04:39.547 position:10% line:83% align:start
-than in our beloved Japan.
-Hey, I'm open!

00:04:39.580 --> 00:04:41.682 position:27% line:83% align:start
They have a very
interesting style.

00:04:41.716 --> 00:04:42.717 position:41% line:89% align:start
It is.

00:04:42.750 --> 00:04:45.653 position:13% line:83% align:start
And I'm happy you haven't
abandoned the game.

00:04:45.686 --> 00:04:47.155 position:30% line:83% align:start
French soccer
is very similar

00:04:47.188 --> 00:04:49.023 position:10% line:89% align:start
to soccer in Latin America,

00:04:49.056 --> 00:04:50.357 position:16% line:89% align:start
because it allows you to

00:04:50.390 --> 00:04:52.560 position:21% line:83% align:start
-grow independently.
-I'm open! Pass!

00:04:52.593 --> 00:04:55.362 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's practically
a more artistic style.

00:04:55.395 --> 00:04:56.664 position:41% line:83% align:start
Wooh!
We can do this!

00:04:56.697 --> 00:04:58.431 position:33% line:83% align:start
Hey, listen,
what do you say...

00:04:58.465 --> 00:05:01.269 position:21% line:83% align:start
if we practice like
the good old days, huh?

00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:02.302 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Mhm.
-Here! Get the ball!

00:05:02.335 --> 00:05:04.238 position:13% line:89% align:start
I thought you'd never ask!

00:05:04.272 --> 00:05:05.139 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Hey, guys...
-Over here!

00:05:05.173 --> 00:05:06.908 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Can we play?
-Yeah!

00:05:06.941 --> 00:05:08.509 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hey, man, pass the ball!

00:05:08.543 --> 00:05:09.777 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hey!
-Get the ball!

00:05:09.811 --> 00:05:11.746 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:13.648 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wow, he's fast.

00:05:14.882 --> 00:05:15.750 position:35% line:89% align:start
Misaki...

00:05:16.584 --> 00:05:17.952 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Genzo]
 <i>Tsubasa...</i>

00:05:17.985 --> 00:05:22.389 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>He has everything he needs</i>
 <i>to play professionally.</i>

00:05:22.422 --> 00:05:23.925 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>He is incredible.</i>

00:05:23.958 --> 00:05:25.193 position:38% line:83% align:start
Ready?
Here we go!

00:05:25.226 --> 00:05:26.459 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:05:26.493 --> 00:05:28.529 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Genzo]
 <i>Taro Misaki...</i>

00:05:28.563 --> 00:05:31.632 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>is a soccer genius.</i>

00:05:31.666 --> 00:05:32.200 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:05:32.233 --> 00:05:33.134 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:05:33.167 --> 00:05:34.434 position:16% line:89% align:start
Misaki, you're amazing.

00:05:34.467 --> 00:05:36.403 position:21% line:83% align:start
Can you tell us how
we can shoot like that?

00:05:36.436 --> 00:05:38.272 position:30% line:83% align:start
Well, honestly,
it's not that difficult.

00:05:38.306 --> 00:05:39.406 position:33% line:89% align:start
You just...

00:05:39.439 --> 00:05:40.741 position:27% line:83% align:start
have to practice
with the ball

00:05:40.775 --> 00:05:43.277 position:24% line:83% align:start
every single day
and without fail.

00:05:43.311 --> 00:05:44.779 position:24% line:83% align:start
That will give you
the skills you need

00:05:44.812 --> 00:05:45.345 position:30% line:89% align:start
to control it.

00:05:45.378 --> 00:05:46.314 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:48.082 position:33% line:83% align:start
But the most
important thing...

00:05:48.115 --> 00:05:49.684 position:21% line:83% align:start
is to become friends
with the ball.

00:05:49.717 --> 00:05:51.819 position:16% line:83% align:start
A good friend from Japan
taught me that.

00:05:51.853 --> 00:05:53.453 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:05:56.757 --> 00:05:58.826 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Genzo] <i>I'm sending you</i>
 <i>the picture from that day</i>

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:01.562 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>and attached is</i>
 <i>Misaki's address in France.</i>

00:06:01.596 --> 00:06:03.231 position:21% line:77% align:start
-[chuckle]
-[Genzo]
 <i>Tsubasa...</i>

00:06:03.264 --> 00:06:04.364 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>Do everything you can</i>

00:06:04.397 --> 00:06:07.101 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>to become a professional</i>
 <i>soccer player.</i>

00:06:07.134 --> 00:06:08.703 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>Take care of yourself,</i>
 <i>my friend.</i>

00:06:08.736 --> 00:06:11.639 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>Sincerely,</i>
 <i>Genzo Wakabayashi.</i>

00:06:11.672 --> 00:06:13.908 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Tsubasa] <i>So then</i>
 <i>Misaki has been in France</i>

00:06:13.941 --> 00:06:14.976 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>this entire time?</i>

00:06:15.009 --> 00:06:16.110 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>No wonder we never saw him</i>

00:06:16.143 --> 00:06:17.545 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>in tournaments</i>
 <i>here in Japan.</i>

00:06:19.013 --> 00:06:20.715 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>I feel inspired.</i>

00:06:20.748 --> 00:06:23.084 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>Now more than ever,</i>
 <i>I must excel,</i>

00:06:23.117 --> 00:06:24.752 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>so I can be at their level.</i>

00:06:25.887 --> 00:06:28.256 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>They both play at</i>
 <i>a higher level now.</i>

00:06:28.289 --> 00:06:30.258 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>They learned</i>
 <i>the European style.</i>

00:06:30.291 --> 00:06:32.126 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>Now, it's my turn</i>
 <i>to go to Brazil</i>

00:06:32.159 --> 00:06:33.561 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>and play professionally.</i>

00:06:34.295 --> 00:06:35.529 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>And one day...</i>

00:06:35.563 --> 00:06:38.733 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>we'll play in</i>
 <i>the national league.</i>

00:06:38.766 --> 00:06:39.867 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>That...</i>

00:06:39.901 --> 00:06:41.602 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>is my biggest dream.</i>

00:06:42.503 --> 00:06:44.404 position:24% line:83% align:start
All right, Carlos,
break is over.

00:06:44.437 --> 00:06:45.640 position:13% line:89% align:start
We must keep on studying.

00:06:45.673 --> 00:06:48.142 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Portuguese]  É assim que
se fala, garoto.

00:06:48.175 --> 00:06:49.543 position:19% line:89% align:start
Resolvaon exercísson.

00:06:49.577 --> 00:06:51.512 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Tsubasa] [Portuguese]
Será muito fácil.

00:06:53.446 --> 00:06:54.382 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Yukari] What?

00:06:54.414 --> 00:06:56.083 position:27% line:83% align:start
You're leaving
so soon, Hiroshi?

00:06:56.117 --> 00:06:57.285 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yes, I'm sorry.

00:06:57.318 --> 00:06:58.286 position:19% line:89% align:start
I had planned to spend

00:06:58.319 --> 00:06:59.553 position:24% line:83% align:start
some time with you
at your house

00:06:59.587 --> 00:07:02.790 position:16% line:83% align:start
and then keep watching
the Nankatsu team practice,

00:07:02.823 --> 00:07:05.393 position:19% line:83% align:start
but I changed my mind
in the end.

00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:07.361 position:30% line:83% align:start
After watching
one of their games,

00:07:07.395 --> 00:07:09.630 position:24% line:83% align:start
I realized we had
no time to lose.

00:07:09.664 --> 00:07:12.166 position:27% line:83% align:start
We must practice
so we can become stronger.

00:07:12.199 --> 00:07:13.901 position:24% line:83% align:start
Even though we're
a superior team,

00:07:13.935 --> 00:07:15.836 position:16% line:83% align:start
we can't afford to take
any chances.

00:07:15.870 --> 00:07:17.772 position:19% line:83% align:start
Yes, we can't rest on
our laurels.

00:07:17.805 --> 00:07:18.839 position:30% line:89% align:start
We must train.

00:07:18.873 --> 00:07:20.641 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Yep, that's right!
-Yukari, send this message

00:07:20.675 --> 00:07:22.243 position:19% line:89% align:start
to the Nankatsu guys.

00:07:22.276 --> 00:07:23.544 position:13% line:89% align:start
Tell them the Hirado team

00:07:23.577 --> 00:07:25.112 position:35% line:83% align:start
will break
their winning streak

00:07:25.146 --> 00:07:28.683 position:13% line:83% align:start
and we'll be the National
Tournament's new champions.

00:07:32.019 --> 00:07:32.820 position:35% line:89% align:start
[knocking]

00:07:33.621 --> 00:07:35.022 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Takeshi]
Hey, Coach, it's me.

00:07:35.056 --> 00:07:35.957 position:33% line:89% align:start
Come on in.

00:07:36.624 --> 00:07:38.092 position:10% line:89% align:start
We have a huge problem, sir.

00:07:38.125 --> 00:07:40.594 position:21% line:83% align:start
Hyuga disappeared.
We can't find him anywhere.

00:07:40.628 --> 00:07:41.963 position:24% line:89% align:start
What did you say?

00:07:48.069 --> 00:07:50.438 position:10% line:89% align:start
I still can't believe it...

00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.773 position:21% line:83% align:start
He said I'm a tiger
who's lost his fangs.

00:07:56.744 --> 00:07:58.045 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Woah!
-[Ryo] Woah! What?!

00:07:58.079 --> 00:07:59.447 position:19% line:89% align:start
So Misaki's in France?

00:07:59.479 --> 00:08:00.548 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[Tsubasa ]Yep.
-[Ryo] L-Let's see!

00:08:00.581 --> 00:08:02.083 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh, he looks great.

00:08:02.116 --> 00:08:03.951 position:24% line:83% align:start
Oh wow, it's true.
It's him!

00:08:03.985 --> 00:08:05.586 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Look, you guys.
-Ah!

00:08:05.619 --> 00:08:06.454 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Huh?

00:08:06.486 --> 00:08:08.622 position:33% line:83% align:start
Oh, but he's
so handsome.

00:08:08.656 --> 00:08:09.824 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hey, guys, who is he?

00:08:09.857 --> 00:08:11.625 position:13% line:83% align:start
He's a friend that used to
play with us here.

00:08:11.659 --> 00:08:13.561 position:16% line:89% align:start
His name's Taro Misaki.

00:08:13.594 --> 00:08:16.630 position:24% line:83% align:start
He and Tsubasa were
the famous golden duo.

00:08:16.664 --> 00:08:19.166 position:10% line:83% align:start
He was the best in assists,
remember?

00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:20.501 position:24% line:89% align:start
That's impressive.

00:08:20.534 --> 00:08:23.170 position:16% line:83% align:start
I never imagined someone
would be at the Captain's...

00:08:23.204 --> 00:08:24.071 position:41% line:89% align:start
level.

00:08:24.672 --> 00:08:26.707 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>No, Tsubasa is the best.</i>

00:08:26.741 --> 00:08:27.775 position:38% line:83% align:start
Hmm...
You liked Misaki,

00:08:27.808 --> 00:08:28.609 position:33% line:83% align:start
-am I right?
-[gasp]

00:08:28.642 --> 00:08:30.077 position:41% line:83% align:start
Who me?
Of course not.

00:08:30.111 --> 00:08:31.379 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Don't say that.
-[chuckle]

00:08:31.412 --> 00:08:32.646 position:35% line:83% align:start
[narrator]
The Nankatsu School

00:08:32.680 --> 00:08:35.316 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>is close to winning</i>
 <i>the Triple Championship</i>

00:08:35.349 --> 00:08:37.518 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>thanks to its Captain,</i>
 <i>Tsubasa.</i>

00:08:37.551 --> 00:08:39.620 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>While the rival teams</i>
 <i>train very hard</i>

00:08:39.653 --> 00:08:40.654 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>to steal their title</i>

00:08:40.688 --> 00:08:42.390 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>and break</i>
 <i>their winning streak.</i>

00:08:42.423 --> 00:08:43.657 position:24% line:83% align:start
- <i>Hikaru Matsuyama:</i>
-Listen up, guys.

00:08:43.691 --> 00:08:45.326 position:19% line:83% align:start
- <i>Furano Middle School.</i>
-This time, we will beat

00:08:45.359 --> 00:08:46.861 position:24% line:83% align:start
-the Nankatsu team!
-Yes!

00:08:48.029 --> 00:08:49.597 position:5% line:83% align:start
-[narrator] The Tachibana Twins:
-Pay close attention,

00:08:49.630 --> 00:08:50.598 position:16% line:83% align:start
- <i>Hanawa Middle School.</i>
-because as of now,

00:08:50.631 --> 00:08:52.533 position:33% line:83% align:start
we'll become
the new golden duo.

00:08:52.566 --> 00:08:55.603 position:27% line:83% align:start
Get ready to lose
this time, Nankatsu.

00:08:55.636 --> 00:08:57.671 position:19% line:83% align:start
[narrator] Makoto Soda:
 <i>Azumaichi Middle School.</i>

00:08:57.705 --> 00:08:59.874 position:19% line:83% align:start
We will win for sure.
No doubt about it.

00:08:59.907 --> 00:09:00.641 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:09:00.674 --> 00:09:01.976 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Hiroshi] Come on,
work faster!

00:09:02.009 --> 00:09:03.177 position:13% line:83% align:start
-[narrator] Hiroshi Jito:
-We must be ready to beat

00:09:03.210 --> 00:09:05.246 position:16% line:83% align:start
- <i>Hirado Middle School.</i>
-the Nankatsu team.

00:09:05.279 --> 00:09:06.614 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah!

00:09:06.647 --> 00:09:08.549 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>With Nationals</i>
 <i>knocking on their door,</i>

00:09:08.582 --> 00:09:10.785 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>no one wants to leave</i>
 <i>anything to chance</i>

00:09:10.818 --> 00:09:12.553 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>and they're giving it</i>
 <i>their best.</i>

00:09:12.586 --> 00:09:13.621 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:09:13.654 --> 00:09:16.157 position:19% line:83% align:start
[narrator] Meanwhile,
in Okinawa...

00:09:16.190 --> 00:09:17.358 position:24% line:89% align:start
What are you doing?

00:09:17.391 --> 00:09:18.692 position:16% line:89% align:start
You have to move faster!

00:09:18.726 --> 00:09:21.662 position:13% line:83% align:start
No wonder Japanese soccer
has a bad reputation.

00:09:21.695 --> 00:09:22.763 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[grunts]
-Soccer is all about

00:09:22.797 --> 00:09:24.131 position:19% line:89% align:start
strength and agility.

00:09:24.165 --> 00:09:25.299 position:10% line:89% align:start
If you can't kick the water,

00:09:25.332 --> 00:09:26.967 position:27% line:83% align:start
you'll never be
good players.

00:09:27.001 --> 00:09:28.302 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

00:09:28.335 --> 00:09:29.970 position:33% line:89% align:start
Coach Kira.

00:09:30.004 --> 00:09:31.038 position:30% line:89% align:start
So you came...

00:09:31.705 --> 00:09:33.574 position:27% line:89% align:start
Finally, Koijro.

00:09:33.607 --> 00:09:34.809 position:35% line:89% align:start
Yes, sir.

00:09:36.744 --> 00:09:37.945 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Kitazume]
Where's Hyuga?

00:09:37.978 --> 00:09:39.980 position:16% line:83% align:start
If any one of you knows
where he is...

00:09:40.014 --> 00:09:42.583 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-you must tell me right now.

00:09:42.616 --> 00:09:43.684 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Hey, Coach...

00:09:44.652 --> 00:09:46.654 position:13% line:83% align:start
We think that the Captain
went to Okinawa

00:09:46.687 --> 00:09:48.456 position:21% line:89% align:start
to visit Coach Kira.

00:09:48.489 --> 00:09:50.091 position:30% line:83% align:start
What is that?
Who is that?

00:09:50.124 --> 00:09:52.193 position:24% line:83% align:start
I've never heard of
that trainer.

00:09:52.226 --> 00:09:53.694 position:33% line:83% align:start
Do you think
he's in Okinawa?

00:09:53.727 --> 00:09:55.596 position:38% line:83% align:start
Uhh...
Yes, sir.

00:09:55.629 --> 00:09:59.166 position:24% line:83% align:start
How dare he abandon
the school.

00:09:59.200 --> 00:10:00.569 position:16% line:89% align:start
If he got accepted here,

00:10:00.601 --> 00:10:02.870 position:24% line:83% align:start
it was only due to
Miss Kaori's decision.

00:10:02.903 --> 00:10:05.473 position:33% line:83% align:start
You hear me?!
He's on a scholarship!

00:10:05.507 --> 00:10:07.708 position:24% line:83% align:start
Abandoning his team
is irresponsible.

00:10:07.741 --> 00:10:09.043 position:16% line:83% align:start
Please don't you worry,
Coach.

00:10:09.076 --> 00:10:10.678 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'm pretty sure he'll be
back before the tournament.

00:10:10.711 --> 00:10:12.079 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'm not interested.

00:10:12.113 --> 00:10:14.248 position:24% line:83% align:start
He can stay there
for all I care.

00:10:14.281 --> 00:10:16.617 position:21% line:83% align:start
His prep school and
university scholarships

00:10:16.650 --> 00:10:19.153 position:19% line:83% align:start
will be revoked after
such an act.

00:10:19.186 --> 00:10:19.753 position:41% line:83% align:start
-What?
-What?

00:10:19.787 --> 00:10:20.888 position:24% line:89% align:start
Forget about him.

00:10:20.921 --> 00:10:23.023 position:13% line:89% align:start
We'll play without Hyuga.

00:10:23.057 --> 00:10:24.992 position:35% line:83% align:start
-What, sir?
-But coach, sir...

00:10:26.460 --> 00:10:27.828 position:35% line:83% align:start
[narrator]
The previous day...

00:10:29.130 --> 00:10:29.864 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ah...

00:10:29.897 --> 00:10:31.600 position:35% line:83% align:start
Finally,
a moment to rest.

00:10:31.632 --> 00:10:32.766 position:16% line:89% align:start
Man, that was a workout.

00:10:32.800 --> 00:10:35.336 position:33% line:83% align:start
Hey, guys,
according to that magazine,

00:10:35.369 --> 00:10:37.238 position:35% line:83% align:start
we're still
the favorite team.

00:10:37.271 --> 00:10:38.372 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh, lemme see that.

00:10:39.406 --> 00:10:41.976 position:21% line:83% align:start
Oh! They interviewed
Mr. Katagiri.

00:10:42.009 --> 00:10:42.810 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:10:42.843 --> 00:10:44.613 position:16% line:83% align:start
It says they've searched
high and low

00:10:44.645 --> 00:10:46.480 position:24% line:83% align:start
and there's no one
in this country

00:10:46.515 --> 00:10:49.483 position:21% line:83% align:start
capable of defeating
Tsubasa Ozora.

00:10:49.518 --> 00:10:51.051 position:33% line:83% align:start
Well, yeah,
Tsubasa is very good.

00:10:51.085 --> 00:10:53.588 position:16% line:83% align:start
That's true, but I think
he's exaggerating.

00:10:53.622 --> 00:10:55.489 position:16% line:83% align:start
If Hyuga and the others
read this,

00:10:55.524 --> 00:10:57.091 position:24% line:83% align:start
they're going to
lose their minds.

00:10:58.893 --> 00:11:00.794 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Katagiri]
 <i>No, I wasn't exaggerating.</i>

00:11:00.828 --> 00:11:04.732 position:13% line:83% align:start
No one in this country can
rival your talent, kiddo.

00:11:04.765 --> 00:11:06.767 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Katagiri]
 <i>Tsubasa, I really hope</i>

00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:08.537 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>something big happens</i>

00:11:08.570 --> 00:11:09.638 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>in this next tournament...</i>

00:11:09.670 --> 00:11:11.506 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>to put some pressure on you.</i>

00:11:11.540 --> 00:11:12.740 position:27% line:89% align:start
Because if not,

00:11:12.773 --> 00:11:15.109 position:13% line:83% align:start
you won't be able to grow
as a soccer player.

00:11:16.477 --> 00:11:19.680 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I also hope I face someone</i>
 <i>that challenges me.</i>

00:11:19.713 --> 00:11:21.949 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>But even then,</i>
 <i>I won't be defeated.</i>

00:11:21.982 --> 00:11:23.552 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>To earn the right</i>
 <i>to go to Brazil,</i>

00:11:23.585 --> 00:11:25.286 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>I must be the best in Japan.</i>

00:11:25.319 --> 00:11:26.420 position:44% line:83% align:start
[Ryo]
What is this?!

00:11:26.453 --> 00:11:27.288 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:11:27.321 --> 00:11:28.623 position:10% line:89% align:start
What's the matter, Ishizaki?

00:11:28.657 --> 00:11:29.757 position:24% line:89% align:start
What did you read?

00:11:29.790 --> 00:11:31.158 position:27% line:83% align:start
Look at the note
right below.

00:11:31.192 --> 00:11:34.161 position:24% line:83% align:start
It says here Hyuga
has disappeared.

00:11:34.195 --> 00:11:36.297 position:24% line:83% align:start
And they haven't
heard from him...

00:11:36.330 --> 00:11:37.898 position:24% line:89% align:start
in an entire week.

00:11:37.932 --> 00:11:37.998 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:11:44.606 --> 00:11:47.208 position:7% line:83% align:start
[announcer] An enormous typhoon
is ramming the main island

00:11:47.241 --> 00:11:48.577 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>of Okinawa.</i>

00:11:48.610 --> 00:11:50.244 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>We recommend that</i>
 <i>all inhabitants</i>

00:11:50.277 --> 00:11:53.080 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>stay in their homes</i>
 <i>until further notice.</i>

00:11:54.649 --> 00:11:59.353 position:35% line:89% align:start
[yelling]

00:11:59.386 --> 00:12:00.487 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:12:02.423 --> 00:12:04.825 position:35% line:89% align:start
[yelling]

00:12:05.627 --> 00:12:07.261 position:35% line:89% align:start
Take that!

00:12:07.294 --> 00:12:09.396 position:35% line:83% align:start
[yelling]
[grunts]

00:12:14.802 --> 00:12:18.739 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:12:18.772 --> 00:12:20.107 position:27% line:89% align:start
I won't give up.

00:12:20.140 --> 00:12:21.342 position:30% line:89% align:start
Look at that.

00:12:21.375 --> 00:12:22.510 position:19% line:89% align:start
The new guy from Tokyo

00:12:22.544 --> 00:12:23.911 position:30% line:83% align:start
keeps training
against the waves.

00:12:23.944 --> 00:12:25.547 position:35% line:83% align:start
What is he
trying to do, huh?

00:12:25.580 --> 00:12:27.281 position:30% line:83% align:start
You know, man,
that's very dangerous.

00:12:27.314 --> 00:12:29.883 position:27% line:83% align:start
He hasn't stopped
since this morning.

00:12:29.917 --> 00:12:33.521 position:10% line:83% align:start
I found out the coach makes
him train until midnight.

00:12:33.555 --> 00:12:35.222 position:33% line:89% align:start
Get up now!

00:12:35.256 --> 00:12:37.992 position:16% line:83% align:start
I really don't understand
what he's trying to do here.

00:12:39.226 --> 00:12:40.528 position:35% line:83% align:start
[student 2]
Yeah, me neither...

00:12:40.562 --> 00:12:41.462 position:7% line:83% align:start
[narrator] We'll be right back
with Captain Tsubasa.

00:12:41.495 --> 00:12:42.363 position:24% line:89% align:start
but whatever it is,

00:12:42.396 --> 00:12:43.230 position:21% line:83% align:start
it must be important
for him.

00:12:43.264 --> 00:12:47.401 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:12:47.968 --> 00:12:49.303 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>Come on, Kojiro.</i>

00:12:49.336 --> 00:12:52.540 position:35% line:89% align:start
[yeling]

00:12:53.541 --> 00:12:54.441 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:12:54.475 --> 00:12:55.476 position:41% line:89% align:start
 <i>No.</i>

00:12:56.477 --> 00:12:57.478 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>This time...</i>

00:12:59.748 --> 00:13:01.915 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>I don't intend to lose.</i>

00:13:03.484 --> 00:13:05.319 position:27% line:89% align:start
Tsubasa Ozora...

00:13:06.287 --> 00:13:10.024 position:24% line:89% align:start
I will defeat you!

00:13:10.057 --> 00:13:10.659 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:13:10.692 --> 00:13:13.460 position:33% line:89% align:start
[tiger roar]

00:13:13.494 --> 00:13:15.329 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Mr. Kira] <i>Only a shot with</i>
 <i>enough explosive power</i>

00:13:15.362 --> 00:13:18.132 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>is capable of penetrating</i>
 <i>the waves.</i>

00:13:18.165 --> 00:13:19.366 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>Your feet...</i>

00:13:19.400 --> 00:13:24.204 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>are anchored in the sand,</i>
 <i>impeding the incoming waves.</i>

00:13:24.238 --> 00:13:26.473 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>You've finally done it,</i>
 <i>Kojiro.</i>

00:13:27.474 --> 00:13:31.979 position:38% line:89% align:start
[pants]

00:13:32.012 --> 00:13:34.014 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Mr. Kira]
 <i>You've finally awoken...</i>

00:13:34.048 --> 00:13:37.951 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>the true power of the tiger</i>
 <i>within you.</i>

00:13:37.985 --> 00:13:40.689 position:10% line:83% align:start
- <i>Now...go get your prey...</i>
-[panting]

00:13:40.722 --> 00:13:42.557 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>and show him your power.</i>

00:13:42.590 --> 00:13:45.859 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:13:47.061 --> 00:13:49.698 position:19% line:83% align:start
[narrator] The day of
the Tournament has arrived!

00:13:49.731 --> 00:13:51.465 position:21% line:89% align:start
The bus has arrived.

00:13:51.498 --> 00:13:52.701 position:24% line:89% align:start
Everyone, onboard.

00:13:52.734 --> 00:13:54.268 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Uhh... Yeah!
-Uhh... Yeah!

00:13:54.301 --> 00:13:56.837 position:27% line:83% align:start
This can't be.
Hyuga still isn't here.

00:13:56.870 --> 00:13:58.205 position:30% line:89% align:start
What do we do?

00:13:58.238 --> 00:14:00.874 position:10% line:83% align:start
It looks like we'll have to
play without our Captain.

00:14:08.482 --> 00:14:09.416 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Mr. Kira]
Kojiro...

00:14:10.484 --> 00:14:11.753 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kojiro!

00:14:11.786 --> 00:14:15.523 position:35% line:89% align:start
[groaning]

00:14:15.557 --> 00:14:16.190 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wake up, Kojiro.

00:14:16.223 --> 00:14:16.957 position:33% line:83% align:start
[narrator]
And we're back.

00:14:17.759 --> 00:14:18.492 position:35% line:89% align:start
[groaning]

00:14:19.093 --> 00:14:20.528 position:13% line:89% align:start
[reac] Hello, Coach Kira.

00:14:21.962 --> 00:14:24.666 position:16% line:83% align:start
You've finally regained
your spirit.

00:14:24.699 --> 00:14:25.999 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ah...

00:14:26.634 --> 00:14:27.635 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:14:27.669 --> 00:14:30.605 position:13% line:83% align:start
This is an airplane ticket
to Tokyo.

00:14:30.638 --> 00:14:32.005 position:24% line:89% align:start
Now go, Kojiro...

00:14:32.039 --> 00:14:34.241 position:16% line:83% align:start
and show them the power
of the tiger.

00:14:34.274 --> 00:14:35.342 position:35% line:89% align:start
[snicker]

00:14:35.376 --> 00:14:36.377 position:38% line:89% align:start
I will.

00:14:38.045 --> 00:14:39.681 position:35% line:83% align:start
Hurry up.
If we don't hurry up,

00:14:39.714 --> 00:14:41.415 position:24% line:83% align:start
we won't be able to
catch Tsubasa.

00:14:41.448 --> 00:14:43.083 position:19% line:83% align:start
I really would like to
interview him

00:14:43.117 --> 00:14:44.753 position:24% line:83% align:start
before the National
Tournament.

00:14:44.786 --> 00:14:45.986 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yeah, I understand.

00:14:46.788 --> 00:14:49.223 position:30% line:83% align:start
Hey, boss...
Did you see that?

00:14:49.256 --> 00:14:49.923 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:14:50.558 --> 00:14:51.925 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Nozaki]
It's Tsubasa.

00:14:51.959 --> 00:14:53.394 position:19% line:89% align:start
What is he doing here?

00:14:57.164 --> 00:14:58.165 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:15:00.668 --> 00:15:01.636 position:24% line:83% align:start
-No, it can't be.
-[gasp]

00:15:01.669 --> 00:15:03.437 position:30% line:83% align:start
He's actually
trying to do...

00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:06.006 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's not good.
I have a long way to go.

00:15:07.441 --> 00:15:08.442 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>Tsubasa...</i>

00:15:08.475 --> 00:15:11.445 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>You have to learn</i>
 <i>to do my swerve shot.</i>

00:15:11.478 --> 00:15:14.783 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>If not, you won't be able</i>
 <i>to play professionally.</i>

00:15:14.816 --> 00:15:16.116 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>It's a curve shot</i>

00:15:16.150 --> 00:15:18.986 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>that serves to fool</i>
 <i>the goalie.</i>

00:15:19.019 --> 00:15:20.187 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>Tsubasa...</i>

00:15:20.220 --> 00:15:21.922 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>if you master</i>
 <i>this technique,</i>

00:15:21.955 --> 00:15:23.591 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>you'll be ready to play</i>
 <i>in Brazil</i>

00:15:23.625 --> 00:15:25.159 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>and the rest of the world.</i>

00:15:26.761 --> 00:15:27.862 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Tsubasa]
